but your brother just died."

485
00:34:12,391 --> 00:34:14,892
Oh, damn, Byron. I'm sorry to hear that.

486
00:34:14,977 --> 00:34:16,352
I'm not. He was an asshole.

487
00:34:16,436 --> 00:34:18,771
Ran off years ago.
Figured him for dead, anyway.

488
00:34:18,856 --> 00:34:22,817
So, anyway, this lawyer fella says to me,
"Your brother died a rich man."

489
00:34:22,901 --> 00:34:25,611
Oil wells and shit. Close to a million bucks.

490
00:34:25,696 --> 00:34:28,155
GUARD: A million bucks?

491
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:30,616
Fucking incredible
how lucky some assholes get.

492
00:34:30,701 --> 00:34:33,244
Jeez-Louise! Are you gonna see any of that?

493
00:34:33,328 --> 00:34:36,414
35,000. That's what he left me.

494
00:34:36,498 --> 00:34:38,416
- Dollars?
- Yeah.

495
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:41,627
Holy shit! That's great.
That's like winning the sweepstakes.

496
00:34:41,712 --> 00:34:42,920
Isnâ€™t it?

497
00:34:43,005 --> 00:34:46,048
Dumb shit. What do you think
