991
01:09:05,815 --> 01:09:08,192
â™ª Sotto i pini...

992
01:09:08,276 --> 01:09:11,153
(Banging at door) Dufresne?

993
01:09:11,237 --> 01:09:12,821
Dufresne?

994
01:09:12,906 --> 01:09:14,990
Andy, let me out.

995
01:09:17,702 --> 01:09:21,246
Andy?

996
01:09:21,331 --> 01:09:26,502
RED: I have no idea to this day
what those two Italian ladies were singing about.

997
01:09:26,586 --> 01:09:29,004
The truth is, I don't want to know.

998
01:09:29,089 --> 01:09:31,173
Some things are best left unsaid.

999
01:09:35,220 --> 01:09:40,265
I like to think they were singing about something
so beautiful, it can't be expressed in words...

1000
01:09:40,350 --> 01:09:42,726
and makes your heart ache because of it.

1001
01:09:44,938 --> 01:09:47,648
I tell you, those voices soared...

1002
01:09:47,732 --> 01:09:52,277
higher and farther
than anybody in a grey place dares to dream.

1003
01:09:52,362 --> 01:09:55,739
It was like some beautiful bird
flapped into our drab little cage

1004
01:09:55,824 --> 01:09:58,951
and made those walls dissolve away.

1005
01:09:59,035 --> 01:10:01,370
And for the briefest of moments...

1006
01:10:01,454 --> 01:10:04,540
every last man at Shawshank felt free.

1007
01:10:07,043 --> 01:10:09,545
It pissed the Warden off something awful.

1008
01:10:10,964 --> 01:10:12,089
Open the door.

1009
01:10:14,843 --> 01:10:16,760
Open it up!

1010
01:10:17,971 --> 01:10:20,347
Dufresne, open this door!

1011
01:10:20,432 --> 01:10:21,890
(Bangs door)

1012
01:10:21,975 --> 01:10:23,308
Turn that off!

1013
01:10:23,393 --> 01:10:25,477
(Bangs door)

1014
01:10:27,147 --> 01:10:30,024
(Aria continues)

1015
01:10:30,108 --> 01:10:32,860
I am warning you, Dufresne. Turn that off!

1016
01:10:36,364 --> 01:10:38,449
(Increases volume)

1017
01:10:46,708 --> 01:10:48,584
Dufresne...

1018
01:10:49,711 --> 01:10:51,795
You're mine now.

1019
01:10:59,345 --> 01:11:02,097
RED: Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

1020
01:11:02,182 --> 01:11:04,600
(Hadley stops record) On your feet!

1021
01:11:05,810 --> 01:11:07,895
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

1022
01:11:09,397 --> 01:11:13,442
Y-Y-You couldn't play something good, huh?
Hank Williams or something?

1023
01:11:13,526 --> 01:11:16,195
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

1024
01:11:16,279 --> 01:11:18,072
Was it worth it, two weeks in the hole?

1025
01:11:18,156 --> 01:11:19,406
Easiest time I ever did.

1026
01:11:19,491 --> 01:11:22,534
Bullshit!
There's no such thing as easy time in the hole.

1027
01:11:22,535 --> 01:11:25,162
A week in the hole is like a year.

1028
01:11:25,246 --> 01:11:27,956
I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

1029
01:11:28,041 --> 01:11:31,376
So, they let you tote that record player
down there, huh?

1030
01:11:33,505 --> 01:11:35,130
It was in here.

1031
01:11:35,215 --> 01:11:36,882
And in here.

1032
01:11:38,093 --> 01:11:42,346
That's the beauty of music.
They can't get that from you.

1033
01:11:46,267 --> 01:11:48,769
Haven't you ever felt that way about music?

1034
01:11:50,438 --> 01:11:54,525
Well, I played a mean harmonica,
as a younger man.

1035
01:11:54,609 --> 01:11:56,401
Lost interest in it, though.

1036
01:11:56,486 --> 01:11:58,320
Didn't make much sense in here.

1037
01:11:58,404 --> 01:12:00,864
Here's where it makes the most sense.

1038
01:12:00,949 --> 01:12:03,534
You need it, so you don't forget.

1039
01:12:03,618 --> 01:12:04,952
Forget?

1040
01:12:05,036 --> 01:12:06,995
Forget that...

1041
01:12:07,080 --> 01:12:09,164
there are places...

1042
01:12:10,500 --> 01:12:13,043
..in the world that aren't made out of stone...

1043
01:12:13,128 --> 01:12:15,170
that there's a...

1044
01:12:15,255 --> 01:12:17,089
there's something...

1045
01:12:17,173 --> 01:12:19,967
inside that they can't get to...

1046
01:12:20,051 --> 01:12:22,344
that they can't touch.

1047
01:12:22,428 --> 01:12:24,304
It's yours.

1048
01:12:25,723 --> 01:12:27,432
What are you talking about?

1049
01:12:28,518 --> 01:12:30,102
Hope.

1050
01:12:30,186 --> 01:12:32,062
Hope?

1051
01:12:33,898 --> 01:12:36,567
Let me tell you something, my friend.

1052
01:12:36,651 --> 01:12:38,610
Hope is a dangerous thing.

1053
01:12:40,196 --> 01:12:42,239
Hope can drive a man insane.

1054
01:12:43,283 --> 01:12:45,200
It's got no use on the inside.

1055
01:12:45,285 --> 01:12:47,953
You'd better get used to that idea.

1056
01:12:50,373 --> 01:12:51,999
Like Brooks did?

1057
01:13:17,233 --> 01:13:18,275
Sit down.

1058
01:13:23,489 --> 01:13:26,950
It says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

1059
01:13:27,035 --> 01:13:29,661
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1060
01:13:29,746 --> 01:13:31,830
Oh, yes, sir.

1061
01:13:31,831 --> 01:13:33,916
Without a doubt.

1062
01:13:34,959 --> 01:13:37,294
And I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

1063
01:13:39,881 --> 01:13:41,924
No danger to society here.

1064
01:13:42,008 --> 01:13:44,092
God's honest truth.

1065
01:13:46,429 --> 01:13:48,513
Absolutely rehabilitated.

1066
01:13:58,441 --> 01:14:00,525
30 years.

1067
01:14:01,611 --> 01:14:03,654
Jesus, when they say it like that...

1068
01:14:03,738 --> 01:14:05,822
You wonder where it went.

1069
01:14:08,785 --> 01:14:10,869
I wonder where ten years went.

1070
01:14:15,917 --> 01:14:17,209
Here.

1071
01:14:17,293 --> 01:14:19,461
Little parole rejection present.

1072
01:14:21,297 --> 01:14:23,340
Go ahead and open it.

1073
01:14:23,424 --> 01:14:27,219
I had to go through one of your competitors.
I hope you don't mind.

1074
01:14:27,303 --> 01:14:29,388
I wanted it to be a surprise.

1075
01:14:39,524 --> 01:14:41,608
It's very pretty, Andy.

1076
01:14:42,694 --> 01:14:44,778
Thank you.

1077
01:14:46,531 --> 01:14:48,615
Are you going to play it?

1078
01:14:52,745 --> 01:14:54,830
No.

1079
01:14:57,125 --> 01:14:59,209
Not right now.

1080
01:15:04,340 --> 01:15:06,383
(Guards shout)

1081
01:15:06,467 --> 01:15:08,552
Tier 3 South. Clear.

1082
01:15:09,595 --> 01:15:11,638
Tier 4 North. Clear.

1083
01:15:11,723 --> 01:15:13,807
Tier 1 South. Clear.

1084
01:15:16,644 --> 01:15:18,729
Fall in!

1085
01:15:21,441 --> 01:15:23,525
(Gate buzzer)

1086
01:15:51,179 --> 01:15:53,221
(Guard's footsteps)

1087
01:15:53,306 --> 01:15:54,890
Lights out!

1088
01:15:54,974 --> 01:15:56,475
(Click of light switches)

1089
01:16:01,898 --> 01:16:03,982
(Guard walks away)

1090
01:16:10,156 --> 01:16:12,240
(Outer door closes)

1091
01:16:21,084 --> 01:16:23,168
(Gently plays one note)

1092
01:16:28,591 --> 01:16:29,716
(Hammering)

1093
01:16:29,801 --> 01:16:31,843
RED: Andy was as good as his word.

1094
01:16:31,928 --> 01:16:34,429
He wrote two letters a week instead of one.

1095
01:16:37,058 --> 01:16:41,186
In 1959, the State Senate
finally clued into the fact

1096
01:16:41,270 --> 01:16:44,147
they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

1097
01:16:44,232 --> 01:16:50,821
Appropriations Committee voted
an annual payment of $500 just to shut him up.

1098
01:16:50,905 --> 01:16:52,614
And you'd be amazed

1099
01:16:52,698 --> 01:16:54,366
how far Andy could stretch it.

1100
01:16:54,450 --> 01:16:57,327
He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.

1101
01:16:57,412 --> 01:16:59,788
He bought remaindered books by the pound.

1102
01:16:59,872 --> 01:17:02,082
Treasure Island.

1103
01:17:02,166 --> 01:17:04,334
Robert Louis...

1104
01:17:04,419 --> 01:17:05,627
..Stevenson.

1105
01:17:05,711 --> 01:17:07,170
Fiction, adventure.

1106
01:17:09,173 --> 01:17:10,799
What's next?

1107
01:17:10,800 --> 01:17:13,510
I got here Auto Repair and...

1108
01:17:14,554 --> 01:17:15,887
..Soap Carving.

1109
01:17:15,972 --> 01:17:19,349
Trade skills and hobbies. Goes under
Educational. The stack behind you.

1110
01:17:19,434 --> 01:17:21,476
The Count Of Monte Crisco.

1111
01:17:21,561 --> 01:17:23,895
That's Cristo, you dumb shit.

1112
01:17:23,980 --> 01:17:27,774
By Alexandree...Dumass.

1113
01:17:27,859 --> 01:17:32,779
Dumb-ass?

1114
01:17:35,283 --> 01:17:37,617
Dumas. You know what that's about?

1115
01:17:37,702 --> 01:17:39,077
Uh-uh.

1116
01:17:39,162 --> 01:17:41,872
You'll like it. It's about a prison break.

1117
01:17:41,956 --> 01:17:45,959
We ought to file that under Educational, too,
oughtn't we?

1118
01:17:46,043 --> 01:17:50,213
RED: The rest of us did our best to pitch in
when and where we could.

1119
01:17:51,466 --> 01:17:53,300
By the year Kennedy was shot,

1120
01:17:53,384 --> 01:17:57,721
Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of rat turds and turpentine

1121
01:17:57,722 --> 01:18:01,057
into the best prison library in New England,

1122
01:18:01,142 --> 01:18:05,020
complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.

1123
01:18:05,104 --> 01:18:09,274
â™ª Lawd I don't know what I'll do-ooo

1124
01:18:09,358 --> 01:18:12,110
â™ª All I do is sit and sigh...

1125
01:18:12,195 --> 01:18:16,948
RED: That was also the year Warden Norton
instituted his famous Inside Out program.

1126
01:18:17,033 --> 01:18:19,743
You may remember reading about it.

1127
01:18:19,827 --> 01:18:23,246
It made all the papers
and got his picture in Look Magazine.

1128
01:18:23,331 --> 01:18:24,998
No free ride.

1129
01:18:25,082 --> 01:18:28,043
But rather a genuine, progressive advance

1130
01:18:28,127 --> 01:18:30,295
in corrections and rehabilitation.

1131
01:18:31,339 --> 01:18:33,673
Our inmates, properly supervised,

1132
01:18:33,758 --> 01:18:36,510
will be put to work outside these walls,

1133
01:18:36,594 --> 01:18:38,678
performing all manner of public service.

1134
01:18:38,763 --> 01:18:42,682
These men can learn
the value of an honest day's labor,

1135
01:18:42,767 --> 01:18:46,436
while providing a valuable service
to the community and...

1136
01:18:46,521 --> 01:18:51,733
at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. and Mrs. John Q Taxpayer.

1137
01:18:51,817 --> 01:18:54,486
RED: Of course,
Norton failed to mention to the press

1138
01:18:54,570 --> 01:18:57,864
that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

1139
01:18:57,949 --> 01:19:01,117
There are a hundred different ways
to skim off the top.

1140
01:19:01,202 --> 01:19:03,828
Men, materials, you name it.

1141
01:19:04,872 --> 01:19:07,624
And, oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in.

1142
01:19:07,708 --> 01:19:09,834
If this keeps up, you'll put me out of business.

1143
01:19:09,919 --> 01:19:12,087
- Ned!
- This pool of slave labor you've got,

1144
01:19:12,171 --> 01:19:14,214
you can underbid any contractor in town.

1145
01:19:14,298 --> 01:19:18,260
Ned, we're providing
a valuable community service here.

1146
01:19:18,344 --> 01:19:20,595
Well, that's fine for the papers

1147
01:19:20,680 --> 01:19:22,180
but I've got a family to feed.

1148
01:19:22,265 --> 01:19:23,974
Sam...

1149
01:19:24,058 --> 01:19:26,518
Sam, we go back a long way.

1150
01:19:26,602 --> 01:19:28,937
I need this new highway contract.

1151
01:19:29,021 --> 01:19:31,231
I don't get it, and I go under.

1152
01:19:31,315 --> 01:19:33,358
That's a fact.

1153
01:19:33,442 --> 01:19:35,527
You just have some of this fine pie

1154
01:19:35,611 --> 01:19:37,654
my missus made especially for you,

1155
01:19:37,738 --> 01:19:39,072
and you think about that.

1156
01:19:47,123 --> 01:19:50,041
Ned, I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

1157
01:19:50,126 --> 01:19:53,336
It seems to me I already got
my boys committed elsewhere.

1158
01:19:55,214 --> 01:19:57,799
You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.

1159
01:19:59,427 --> 01:20:01,595
RED: And behind every shady deal,

1160
01:20:01,679 --> 01:20:03,888
behind every dollar earned,

1161
01:20:03,973 --> 01:20:07,142
there was Andy, keeping the books.

1162
01:20:08,185 --> 01:20:11,605
Two deposits.
Maine National and New England First.

1163
01:20:11,689 --> 01:20:13,773
Night drops as always, sir.

1164
01:20:44,180 --> 01:20:45,930
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1165
01:20:46,015 --> 01:20:48,808
- Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.
- Yes, sir.

1166
01:20:48,893 --> 01:20:52,646
Tell them if they over-starch my shirts again,
they'll hear about it from me.

1167
01:20:52,730 --> 01:20:54,731
How do I look?

1168
01:20:54,815 --> 01:20:57,525
- Very nice, sir.
- Big charity to-do up Portland way.

1169
01:20:57,610 --> 01:20:59,319
The Governor's going to be there.

1170
01:21:00,738 --> 01:21:02,781
Want the rest of this?

1171
01:21:02,865 --> 01:21:04,949
The woman can't bake worth shit.

1172
01:21:06,327 --> 01:21:08,119
Thank you, sir.

1173
01:21:10,289 --> 01:21:14,042
- He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, I hear.
- What you hear isn't half of it.

1174
01:21:14,126 --> 01:21:16,586
He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of.

1175
01:21:16,671 --> 01:21:18,713
Kickbacks on his kickbacks.

1176
01:21:18,798 --> 01:21:21,675
There's a river of dirty money
running through this place.

1177
01:21:21,759 --> 01:21:25,011
But the problem with having all that money
is you'll have to explain

1178
01:21:25,096 --> 01:21:27,681
- where it came from.
- That's where I come in.

1179
01:21:27,765 --> 01:21:30,266
I channel it, filter it, funnel it.

1180
01:21:30,351 --> 01:21:32,894
Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.

1181
01:21:32,978 --> 01:21:35,647
I send that money out into the real world.

1182
01:21:35,731 --> 01:21:39,359
- And when it comes back...
- Clean as a virgin's honey pot, huh?

1183
01:21:39,443 --> 01:21:40,652
Cleaner.

1184
01:21:40,736 --> 01:21:44,364
By the time Norton retires,
I'll have made him a millionaire.

1185
01:21:47,118 --> 01:21:51,538
If they ever catch on, though, he's gonna
wind up in here wearing a number himself.

1186
01:21:51,622 --> 01:21:54,874
Now, Red, I thought you had
a little more faith in me than that.

1187
01:21:54,959 --> 01:21:58,253
I know you're good, Andy,
but all that paper leaves a trail.

1188
01:21:58,337 --> 01:22:01,339
Now, anybody gets curious,
the FBI, the IRS, whatever,

1189
01:22:01,424 --> 01:22:04,259
it's gonna lead to somebody.

1190
01:22:04,343 --> 01:22:06,302
Sure it is. But not to me.

1191
01:22:06,387 --> 01:22:08,388
And certainly not to the Warden.

1192
01:22:12,435 --> 01:22:13,727
All right. Who?

1193
01:22:13,811 --> 01:22:15,520
Randall Stevens.

1194
01:22:15,604 --> 01:22:16,771
Who?

1195
01:22:17,857 --> 01:22:22,569
The silent silent partner. He's the guilty one,
Your Honor. The man with the bank accounts.

1196
01:22:22,653 --> 01:22:24,821
That's where the filtering process starts.

1197
01:22:24,905 --> 01:22:28,074
If they trace anything,
it's just going to lead to him.

1198
01:22:28,159 --> 01:22:29,743
But who is he?

1199
01:22:29,827 --> 01:22:31,870
He's a phantom, an apparition.

1200
01:22:31,954 --> 01:22:33,913
Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.

1201
01:22:33,998 --> 01:22:36,166
I conjured him...

1202
01:22:36,250 --> 01:22:38,293
out of thin air.

1203
01:22:38,377 --> 01:22:41,212
He doesn't exist, except on paper.

1204
01:22:44,341 --> 01:22:46,718
Andy, you canâ€™t just make a person up.

1205
01:22:46,802 --> 01:22:49,929
Sure you can, if you know how
the system works, where the cracks are.

1206
01:22:50,014 --> 01:22:53,516
It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.

1207
01:22:53,601 --> 01:22:56,227
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate,

1208
01:22:56,312 --> 01:22:58,646
a driver's license, social security number.

1209
01:22:58,731 --> 01:22:59,939
You're shitting me?

1210
01:23:00,024 --> 01:23:01,983
If they ever trace any of those accounts,

1211
01:23:02,067 --> 01:23:04,944
they're going to wind up chasing
a figment of my imagination.

1212
01:23:05,029 --> 01:23:07,113
Well, I'll be damned.

1213
01:23:08,407 --> 01:23:10,450
Did I say you were good?

1214
01:23:10,534 --> 01:23:12,702
Shit, you're a Rembrandt!

1215
01:23:12,787 --> 01:23:14,829
You know, the funny thing is,

1216
01:23:14,914 --> 01:23:18,875
on the outside, I was an honest man,
straight as an arrow.

1217
01:23:19,919 --> 01:23:22,295
I had to come to prison to be a crook.

1218
01:23:31,055 --> 01:23:32,430
Ever bother you?

1219
01:23:33,474 --> 01:23:36,893
I don't run the scams, Red,
I just process the profits.

1220
01:23:36,977 --> 01:23:39,020
Fine line maybe but...

1221
01:23:39,104 --> 01:23:41,815
I also built that library

1222
01:23:41,899 --> 01:23:44,526
and used it to help a dozen guys
get a high school diploma.

1223
01:23:44,610 --> 01:23:46,486
Why do you think the Warden lets me do it?

1224
01:23:46,570 --> 01:23:49,322
To keep you happy and doing the laundry.

1225
01:23:49,406 --> 01:23:51,533
Money instead of sheets.

1226
01:23:51,617 --> 01:23:54,327
Well, I work cheap. That's the trade-off.

1227
01:23:54,411 --> 01:23:56,496
(Siren wails)

1228
01:23:59,917 --> 01:24:02,126
â™ª JOHNNY OTIS: Willy And The Hand Jive

1229
01:24:09,927 --> 01:24:11,719
â™ª I know a cat named...

1230
01:24:11,804 --> 01:24:14,472
RED: Tommy Williams
came to Shawshank in 1965

1231
01:24:14,557 --> 01:24:16,599
on a two-year stretch for B&E.

1232
01:24:16,684 --> 01:24:18,810
That's breaking and entering to you.

1233
01:24:18,894 --> 01:24:23,523
The cops caught him sneaking TV sets
out the back door of a JC Penney.

1234
01:24:23,607 --> 01:24:25,358
Young punk.

1235
01:24:25,442 --> 01:24:27,485
Mr. Rock'n'roll.

1236
01:24:27,570 --> 01:24:29,237
Cocky as hell.

1237
01:24:29,321 --> 01:24:31,906
Hey, come on, old boys! Moving like molasses!

1238
01:24:31,991 --> 01:24:33,950
Making me look bad.

1239
01:24:33,951 --> 01:24:35,910
RED: We liked him immediately.

1240
01:24:35,995 --> 01:24:38,037
So I'm backing out the door, right?

1241
01:24:38,122 --> 01:24:39,831
And I got the TV like this.

1242
01:24:39,915 --> 01:24:43,751
It was a big old thing. I couldn't see shit.
Suddenly, I hears this voice.

1243
01:24:43,836 --> 01:24:45,879
"Freeze, kid! Hands in the air."

1244
01:24:45,963 --> 01:24:47,630
Well, I just stand there,

1245
01:24:47,715 --> 01:24:50,508
holding onto that TV. So, finally, the voice says,

1246
01:24:50,593 --> 01:24:52,552
"Do you hear what I said, boy?"

1247
01:24:52,636 --> 01:24:55,013
I say, "Yes, sir, I sure did.

1248
01:24:55,097 --> 01:24:58,725
But if I drop this fucking thing,
you got me on destruction of property, too."

1249
01:24:58,809 --> 01:25:00,935
(Laughter)

1250
01:25:02,813 --> 01:25:05,523
Hey, you've done a stretch in Cashman, right?

1251
01:25:05,608 --> 01:25:09,444
Yeah. Yeah, that was an easy piece of time,
let me tell you.

1252
01:25:09,528 --> 01:25:12,155
Weekend furloughs, work programs.

1253
01:25:12,239 --> 01:25:13,656
Not like here.

1254
01:25:13,741 --> 01:25:16,075
Sounds like you done time
all over New England.

1255
01:25:16,160 --> 01:25:21,247
Yeah, I've been in and out since I was 13. You
name the place, chances are I've been there.

1256
01:25:21,332 --> 01:25:25,335
Perhaps it's time you tried a new profession?

1257
01:25:25,419 --> 01:25:30,506
What I mean is, you don't seem to be a good
